'''Lelang Tomb Mound Cluster''' (楽浪古墳群) is a cluster of ancient tomb mounds excavated from the southern to eastern areas of the site of the administrative center of [[:en:Lelang Commandery|Lelang Commandery]], a colony established on the {{ill|Korean Peninsula|ja|朝鮮半島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Korean Peninsula|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} by the [[:en:Han dynasty|Han dynasty]]’s [[:en:Emperor Wu of Han|Emperor Wu of Han]] in [[:en:108 BC|108 BC]].<ref name="Lelang Tomb Mound Cluster">{{Kotobank|楽浪古墳群|[[:en:Heibonsha World Encyclopedia|Encyclopedia of the World]]}}</ref> According to the prevailing academic theory, the location of [[:en:Lelang Commandery|Lelang Commandery]] corresponds to present-day {{ill|Pyongyang|ja|平壌直轄市|lt=Pyongyang City|lt_ja=平壌市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Pyongyang|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 平壌市}} and its surroundings.<ref>{{Cite news|author=|date=2015-12-14|title=“Misinterpretation of the Creation Date of Historical Materials” – A professor at Hanbock University refutes the theory that “the Great Wall of Myriad Li reaches Pyongyang”|publisher=|newspaper=[[:en:The Dong-A Ilbo|Dong-A Ilbo]]|url=https://www.donga.com/jp/article/all/20151214/430197/1|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20221027105756/https://www.donga.com/jp/article/all/20151214/430197/1|archivedate=2022-10-27}}</ref> In the area around {{ill|Pyongyang|ja|平壌直轄市|lt=Pyongyang City|lt_ja=平壌市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Pyongyang|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 平壌市}} and the [[:en:Rangrang-guyok|Lelang area]], particularly near Jeongbaek-dong, over a thousand tomb mounds are found clustered together.<ref name="Lelang Tomb Mound Cluster"/>
